# Verify before done

“Done” requires evidence in the same session, not confidence.

## By touch surface

| Touched paths | Minimum verification |
|---------------|------------------------|
| `engine/**`, `extension/**` | `just build` (and `just regress` if SQL/C wrappers or `.sql.in` changed) |
| `app/**` | `just build` + relevant `dotnet test` / `just test` if tests exist for the project |
| `db/migrations/**` | `just db-up` (or document why not run) |
| Hot-path / determinism claims | `just verify` |
| Docker daemon off / SSH agent work | `just test-no-docker` (not `just test`) |

## After edits

- Run `ReadLints` on every file you edited.
- If build/test fails, fix or report the failure — do not hand-wave.

## Response shape when finishing implementation

1. What changed (1–3 bullets).
2. What you ran (exact commands + pass/fail).
3. What remains (issue subtasks, follow-ups).

If you did not run verification, label the work **unverified** and say what command the user should run.
